Learning the ropes
In conversation with industry professionals…
Dear {!Lead.FirstName}
Our upcoming Learning the Ropes event is an opportunity for students in Years 9 to 12 and their parents to talk with industry representatives and our Alumni, providing practical insights into the workplace of today.
We are delighted to be joined by representatives from a range of industries including business, medicine, law, engineering, science, design and architecture, hospitality, performing arts and media and communication. The evening includes:
Very special guest and key note speaker Mr Greg Cowell OA 1988, Practice Lead & Solution Implementation, Sofico Services Australia on careers, how they may evolve, innovations and life-long learning; Technical Workshops on resume writing, interview presentation, personal workplace branding; Career professionals from OAA, Hessian Club, City Learning and the SACS community available to chat directly and answer questions; and Tertiary students to provide helpful hints on how to cope with school/study/work transition.
If you would like to attend the workshops on resume writing, personal branding and interview skills, please book that workshop when you book online.
When: Thursday 20 July
Where: St Andrew’s Cathedral School, Senior College Campus, Bishop Barry Centre, 51 Druitt Street, Sydney
Time: 5.30 for a 6pm start – 8.30pm
Bookings essential. Book online now: https://www.trybooking.com/QRDG
I do hope you and and your family can join us for this extraordinary event as we support our students in preparing for life beyond school.
Kind regards
Bruce Perry Registrar/Mathematics Teacher
